1
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,359
Another new day.

2
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:13,120
How wonderful.

3
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,760
Time for breakfast.

4
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:18,760
I'm not hungry.

5
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:19,519
But...

6
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:21,840
Skipping breakfast is bad for you.

7
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:22,719
I know.

8
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,439
I'm perfectly healthy, aren't I?

9
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,000
Fine. Food's in the pot.

10
00:01:27,519 --> 00:01:28,719
Heat it up when you're hungry.

11
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:30,879
You're heading out?

12
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:31,760
Yeah.

13
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,120
Uncle Cripple's crutch is broken.

14
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:34,959
Needs fixing.

15
00:01:35,359 --> 00:01:37,239
Brother Fool's candy is gone too.

16
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:39,640
Grandpa An's made up a new story.

17
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,840
I want to go see them all.

18
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,159
Such drama queens.

19
00:01:44,799 --> 00:01:45,760
No going out for a while.

20
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,640
Why?

21
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:52,879
I'm the boss.

22
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:53,840
I pay the wages.

23
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,400
So no skipping work.

24
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:58,519
Fine.

25
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,359
No going out on weekends either.

26
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,439
You're working overtime.

27
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:03,959
I'll pay overtime.

28
00:02:04,799 --> 00:02:06,280
Is it my condition?

29
00:02:06,519 --> 00:02:07,840
Has it gotten worse again?

30
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,639
How much longer do I have?

31
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,680
A long time.

32
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,360
Mom used to say...

33
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:22,159
everyone dies eventually.

34
00:02:23,039 --> 00:02:25,240
And according to the doctors,

35
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,960
I shouldn't have lived this long.

36
00:02:27,759 --> 00:02:30,120
So every day I'm still alive,

37
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,479
I'm truly grateful.

38
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,680
So can Brother Su Yang tell me...

39
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:35,800
how much longer I have?

40
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,560
I told you.

41
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,199
You'll keep living.

42
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:52,599
Three months.

43
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,360
Three months.

44
00:02:54,439 --> 00:02:55,240
That's plenty.

45
00:02:55,719 --> 00:02:57,039
That gives me enough time

46
00:02:57,159 --> 00:02:58,919
to fix Uncle Cripple's crutch,

47
00:02:59,159 --> 00:03:00,719
buy candy for Brother Fool,

48
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,520
and hear Grandpa An's story.

49
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:03,199
Oh, right.

50
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,280
Sister Qiu Ge's remote needs new batteries too.

51
00:03:05,879 --> 00:03:07,439
What does any of this have to do with you?

52
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,639
Can't you do something for yourself?

53
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:13,879
I've already done what I need to.

54
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:16,759
Doing something for others

55
00:03:16,879 --> 00:03:19,080
is the last meaning of my existence.

56
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,479
Grandpa An's show...

57
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,520
if I don't go,

58
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,759
he won't have an audience.

59
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:25,199
Also...

60
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,159
I'll go buy you more medicine tomorrow.

61
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,479
And...

62
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:29,439
as long as I don't let you go,

63
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:31,599
you're not going to die.

64
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,159
Not even Death himself can take you.

65
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,159
Every immortal has their own Artifact.

66
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:58,719
And after long-term nurturing,

67
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:01,319
they leave their Will upon the Artifact.

68
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:06,080
Do you know what that means?

69
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:07,800
Spit it out.

70
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,840
It means the Artifact gets a patina.

71
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,319
Try saying something useful.

72
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:14,120
What, you polishing prayer beads?

73
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:16,399
What it means is,

74
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,399
aside from the immortals themselves,

75
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,480
their Artifacts

76
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,920
can also use their lingering Will

77
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:24,360
to seek out a suitable Blessed One.

78
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,120
Do you get it now?

79
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:28,240
Nope, don't get it.

80
00:04:30,839 --> 00:04:31,720
Let me put it this way.

81
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,920
If you found Zhurong's Artifact

82
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,480
and absorbed the Will inside it,

83
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:40,079
your power would skyrocket.

84
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:45,600
This is huge information.

85
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:47,560
Wang Qiusheng,

86
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:50,839
you're practically my benefactor!

87
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:01,279
An Artifact can nourish those of the same origin.

88
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:06,079
Isn't that exactly what only Immortal Seeds can do?

89
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:08,360
So then, the Artifacts—

90
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,720
where would one find them?

91
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:16,800
I'm sure our benefactor Wang Qiusheng

92
00:05:17,279 --> 00:05:18,959
is wondering the same thing.

93
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,399
The museum.

94
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,720
It's gotta be the museum.

95
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:30,920
Just think about it.

96
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,360
Artifacts left over from ancient times—

97
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,959
those are antiques.

98
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:36,120
So,

99
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:38,920
they might be kept in a museum.

100
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,160
If I can think of this,

101
00:05:41,399 --> 00:05:43,439
our benefactor Wang Qiusheng,

102
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:44,920
who's been planning this for so long,

103
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,879
must have figured it out too.

104
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,439
He's not the indecisive type.

105
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,079
So tonight,

106
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:57,480
he just might

107
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,920
go test his luck.

108
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:02,920
Give it here.

109
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:12,959
I want a map.

110
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,199
I don't buy it.

111
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:30,720
No way Wang Qiusheng has only this one ancient text.

112
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,360
So we can find him,

113
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,319
shake him down for a second one,

114
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:36,160
then let him go,

115
00:06:36,399 --> 00:06:38,439
and we'll get a third,

116
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,720
and a fourth.

117
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:43,000
He's basically a treasure-hunting rat.

118
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,279
Send a few of your top men

119
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,879
to this museum

120
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,720
to lie in wait

121
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,519
for our benefactor.

122
00:07:05,199 --> 00:07:06,000
Wait, something's off.

123
00:07:07,279 --> 00:07:09,959
If Liu Chengfeng was so sure he could catch me,

124
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,639
why would he give me a chance to escape?

125
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,560
He's bluffing me.

126
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,480
If I go to Qiushui City now,

127
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,160
or Chuncao City,

128
00:07:27,959 --> 00:07:29,040
or even the Imperial Capital,

129
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,079
I can still start over.

130
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:35,759
But before I leave,

131
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,120
the Shanhai Scripture Vault—

132
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,480
if I could find an Artifact here,

133
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:03,160
even a broken one...

134
00:08:12,839 --> 00:08:13,879
Call the young master.

135
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:14,800
Move.

136
00:09:16,279 --> 00:09:17,519
Hello there, benefactor.

137
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:19,120
Didn't expect us to meet again

138
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,600
so soon.

139
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,440
Got any more ancient texts?

140
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:22,159
Toss me one,

141
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,399
and I'll still let you go.

142
00:09:26,039 --> 00:09:26,559
Oh, right—

143
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,480
just a heads-up:

144
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,519
if you run out of stock,

145
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,120
you'll have to go find more.

146
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,840
One ancient text,

147
00:09:33,159 --> 00:09:33,879
one life.

148
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:35,679
I'm very reasonable.

149
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:50,679
Off you go.

150
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:51,759
Hold on.

151
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,279
Leave the bag too.

152
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,039
Very good.

153
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,480
Bye-bye.

154
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:09,320
Well, that really wasn't hard at all.

155
00:10:21,759 --> 00:10:22,480
Sure,

156
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:26,080
I lost an ancient text,

157
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:30,159
but you all overlooked

158
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:35,159
that I got an Artifact.

159
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,279
A museum...

160
00:10:43,759 --> 00:10:44,519
...replica.

161
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,120
This thing...

162
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:48,000
Even this thing is a fake!

163
00:10:51,279 --> 00:10:52,879
Shameless Shanhai City!

164
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,519
If Shanhai City won't have me,

165
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,080
then I'll go to the Imperial Capital!

166
00:10:58,919 --> 00:10:59,840
One day,

167
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,960
I'll rise again!

168
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,120
I will...

169
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,279
I will personally avenge this!

170
00:11:08,799 --> 00:11:10,559
Personally avenge this!

171
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:19,679
Can we talk?

172
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:22,159
Who are you?

173
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,200
Past-With-The-Wind.

174
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,240
Right.

175
00:11:25,799 --> 00:11:27,440
I'm Liu from Shanhai City.

176
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:33,840
I am...

177
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,360
Past-With-The-Wind.

178
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,519
Right.

179
00:11:37,759 --> 00:11:38,519
Past-With-The-Wind.

180
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,679
Last night I read an ancient text.

181
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,279
It had information about Tongtong's illness.

182
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:48,120
I've been curious for a while now.

183
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,759
About Tongtong's illness.

184
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:52,200
Three years ago, shouldn't it have...

185
00:11:54,879 --> 00:11:55,559
Sorry.

186
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:58,000
Let me finish, all right?

187
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,559
According to the ancient records,

188
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:02,360
Tongtong's constitution

189
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:04,440
is called a Celestial Blight Body.

190
00:12:04,759 --> 00:12:07,399
It instinctively rejects Immortal Energy,

191
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,200
yet is severely deficient in it.

192
00:12:09,799 --> 00:12:12,200
Ultimately, it causes blood disorders.

193
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,919
So the only way is through external means,

194
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:15,600
forcibly injecting Immortal Energy,

195
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,440
to keep all the organs in her body

196
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,519
functioning.

197
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,519
But as time goes on,

198
00:12:21,879 --> 00:12:23,440
her demand for the quality of Immortal Energy

199
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,279
will only grow higher.

200
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:28,960
So if I'm not mistaken,

201
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,639
up until now,

202
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:33,519
you've been using items with trace Immortal Energy

203
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,720
to keep Tongtong alive, right?

204
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,279
And now,

205
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,399
items of that level,

206
00:12:38,399 --> 00:12:40,000
of that quality,

207
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,240
no longer work on her condition.

208
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,799
Go on.

209
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,480
So the perfect solution right now

210
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,919
would be to kill a true Immortal.

211
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:52,879
That way,

212
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,080
Tongtong's complications over the next few years

213
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,320
wouldn't get any worse.

214
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,960
But from the looks of it now,

215
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,279
that doesn't seem realistic.

216
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:01,480
Of course,

217
00:13:01,799 --> 00:13:03,360
I have a second option.

218
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,480
Next time in front of me,

219
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,720
if you leave a sentence half-finished,

220
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,799
it'll be your windpipe I slit.

221
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,120
Artifact. An Artifact.

222
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:17,039
According to the ancient records,

223
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:19,399
Artifacts are treasures left behind by Immortals.

224
00:13:19,519 --> 00:13:22,200
They contain the purest Immortal Energy.

225
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,720
So even with the passage of time,

226
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:25,960
and a bit of depletion,

227
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,360
using one to heal Tongtong

228
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,440
would still be more than enough.

229
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,879
Now then, let's talk

230
00:13:31,919 --> 00:13:33,840
about the Artifact in your hands.

231
00:13:34,559 --> 00:13:35,200
I...

232
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,519
Brother Su Yang is a really nice guy.

233
00:13:38,519 --> 00:13:39,799
He's just joking with you.

234
00:13:39,799 --> 00:13:40,279
Right.

235
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:40,840
Let me patch you up.

236
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,639
Just kidding.

237
00:13:41,679 --> 00:13:43,000
The wound isn't serious.

238
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,720
Rest a couple of days and you'll be fine.

239
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:45,919
It won't leave a scar.

240
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:46,919
Thank you.

241
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:49,279
Now, where were we?

242
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:49,960
The Artifact.

243
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,120
Right.

244
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:52,679
The Artifact.

245
00:13:54,039 --> 00:13:54,759
Next month,

246
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,879
the Imperial Capital will hold a Blessed Ones Tournament.

247
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,360
First prize is an Artifact...

248
00:14:01,159 --> 00:14:02,559
...fragment.

249
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Even though it's just a fragment,

250
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,799
it still contains a Will within it.

251
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,759
That alone is extraordinary.

252
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,080
Blessed Ones Tournament.

253
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,159
Right.

254
00:14:12,399 --> 00:14:13,279
Anything else?

255
00:14:13,639 --> 00:14:14,399
Aren't you...

256
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,360
planning to enter?

257
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,120
I am entering.

258
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,399
Now that I know,

259
00:14:20,679 --> 00:14:21,559
I'll go on my own.

260
00:14:23,399 --> 00:14:24,840
I think I forgot to mention,

261
00:14:25,759 --> 00:14:28,480
only the most powerful teams from each city

262
00:14:28,559 --> 00:14:29,759
are eligible to compete.

263
00:14:34,679 --> 00:14:35,840
I just tested it for you.

264
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:36,960
The water temperature is just right.

265
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,720
You must be thirsty.

266
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:39,759
Not really.

267
00:14:41,559 --> 00:14:43,120
That thing you asked me to join...

268
00:14:43,159 --> 00:14:44,000
Captain of whatever team...

269
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:44,840
I agree to do it.

270
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:49,240
You're not going to resign

271
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,320
the moment the tournament ends, are you?

272
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:51,840
No.

273
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,360
The first thing I'll do

274
00:14:54,399 --> 00:14:55,720
is treat Tongtong's illness.

275
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:56,799
Resigning will be the second thing.

276
00:14:57,639 --> 00:14:58,519
Okay, okay, okay.

277
00:14:58,799 --> 00:14:59,559
Even so,

278
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,159
I still need to explain something to you.

279
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:02,679
In Shanhai City,

280
00:15:02,799 --> 00:15:05,200
though the Liu family has some influence,

281
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,879
there's still the Council of Elders above us,

282
00:15:07,159 --> 00:15:09,159
which creates chains of vested interests.

283
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:10,279
So,

284
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:13,360
the Council won't let me handle it all alone.

285
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,159
They'll definitely plant some people

286
00:15:16,399 --> 00:15:17,720
they want to push forward.

287
00:15:18,039 --> 00:15:20,320
Then they'll stage what looks like

288
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:23,039
a perfectly fair qualifying match.

289
